### How to prevent page Caching
* Pages are cached by the browser and web server
* Requests for pages are fulfilled first from the cache


### Use Pragmas to Prevent Caching
* Must be set before any HTML is produced
* See "bacs350/demo/25/index.php" for example code

```php
<?php

    header("Pragma: no-cache");
    header("Expires: 0");
    header("Cache-Control: no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate");
?>

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        ...
    </head>
    <body>
        ...
    </body>
</html>
```


### Use Pragmas to Prevent Caching
* Must be set before any HTML is produced
* See "bacs350/demo/26/views.php" for example code
* Review "render_page" function


